snippet.textDisplay: pro tip: Take that bag and submerge it in water and leave a 1 inch opening in the bag to let air out. Submerge the whole bag (Minus the opening in the bag) under water. The water's pressure will force all the air out of the opening in the bag and create a vacuum seal in the bag. This will make fish last longer and be fresher as there will be virtually no frost bite given there is no air :D. I just learnt this TODAY actually after spearing some sheepshead here in Florida and tried it in a big bowl of water. Super simple!

snippet.textDisplay:
Hey bud,


I'm so sorry about everything that is happening in Australia. I can not tell you how devasted we are. We have donated but obviously, something is never enough.

But... if you can, make it out to Nicaragua to do some real tarpon fishing. At our property, they are weighing between 150-180lbs. PLEASE send me an email and you guys have a place to stay, eat and simply hangout. Between the coffee farm and the fishing, I think you guys will have plenty of footage for weeks. Get there! I know its a trek but lets have you guys surf and fish in "boats" you never thought possible, I guarantee you won't regret it. (Brodie, Jackson, Jarrad, and Sam, you guys would be in for a trip)

It would be an unbelievable experience for all of you. FYI, Jared, we have bull sharks and sawfish swimming 190km upriver into the largest lake of Central America.

See you guys in Nicaragua,

Jorge
